headline: American Express Faces 10% Rate Cap Debate And Valuation Questions
summary: U.S. lawmakers have put forward a proposal to cap credit card interest rates at 10%. The plan is aimed at consumer borrowing costs and would apply across major issuers, including American Express (NYSE:AXP). Industry leaders, including JPMorgan's CEO, have publicly criticized the proposal, calling it an "economic disaster."
